courses.learning_outcomes:
After taking this course, students are expected to:

(1)be able to use the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA) and the IPA symbols provided in dictionaries;
(2)understand, compare and hypothesize on the production of speech sounds (place of articulation, differences and common points…);
(3)understand and describe the rhythmic groups and intonation patterns of modern French;
(4)be able to pronounce/read out modern French and analyze phenomenon of spoken French;
(5)be able to play with words sonority and create short rhymes/ poems/ songs…
